+#!/bin/bash
+
+set -euo pipefail
+ROOT="$(cd "$(dirname "$0")" && pwd -P)"
+PACKAGE="${1:-}"
+
+if [ -z "$PACKAGE" ]; then
+  PACKAGE="$(/usr/bin/osascript -e 'POSIX path of (choose file with prompt "Choose a signed .dreamskin theme package")')" || exit 0
+fi
+
+exec "$ROOT/scripts/import-dreamskin-macos.sh" --file "$PACKAGE"
diff --git a/macos/README.md b/macos/README.md
index 0653f5b..59841c9 100644
--- a/macos/README.md
+++ b/macos/README.md
@@ -55,6 +55,29 @@ To build the “double-click install” folder layout for non-git users:
 
 That ZIP contains a visible installer plus a hidden `.codex-dream-skin-studio` engine. Do not ship only CSS/images.
 
+## Import a signed `.dreamskin` package
+
+Double-click `Import Dream Skin.command`, or use the installed engine directly:
+
+```bash
+~/.codex/codex-dream-skin-studio/scripts/import-dreamskin-macos.sh \
+  --file "$HOME/Downloads/theme.dreamskin"
+```
+
+Import verifies the closed MVP v1 manifest, Ed25519 signature, ZIP structure,
+resource hashes, image container and decoded dimensions before committing an
+immutable version under Application Support. Installation does not apply the
+theme. Add `--apply` only after reviewing the source and package information.
+
+The installer also registers `dreamskin://install` links and `.dreamskin` files
+to a small per-user app in `~/Applications`. Store links show the source host,
+declared size and theme hint before downloading. Downloads require public HTTPS,
+are capped at 20 MiB and three redirects, and must match the declared SHA-256.
+Applying the installed theme is always a separate confirmation.
+
+The bundled `codex-skin.sample.2026-01` key is a public interoperability fixture
+key and is not production publishing authority.
+
 ## How it works (security boundary)
 
 1. Discover `com.openai.codex` and validate signature / Team ID / arch / bundled Node.
diff --git a/macos/assets/dreamskin-handler.applescript b/macos/assets/dreamskin-handler.applescript
